The course will analyze the process of representation as it appears in ethnographic texts. The reading material will provide a basis to discuss the insider and outsider perspective of an individual or community, representational positions discernible in ethnographic writing, relevant metadiscursive practices,  and their historical context.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to provide an overview of the evolvement of textual representations in culture studies. This course will develop critical thinking as well as the capacity to analyze ethnographic representations, which form a necessary foundation for writing academic research.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student  -will be able to do an independent and critical analysis on the theoretical and methodological aspects of ethnographic representations; -will improve her/his academic writing and oral presentation skills.
